      "writtenOn": "2018-05-18T22:24:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s annoying to have to check several different files just to figure out what the test is testing. Here, for example, it may be easier to read if you could just inline the contents of testdata/4/stdlib/init.sky instead of making the reader look at some other file. And going the other way, a reader looking at testdata/4/stdlib/init.sky has no idea what imported_builtin is until reading interpreter_test.go. Much of the testdata is several tiny files that only make sense once you\u0027ve read all of them and also seen interpreter_test.go.\n\nHow much effort would be needed to just be able to supply the contents of these files to run directly instead of as file paths?\n\nOne approach I can think of would be to give Interpreter an optional function to use to read files in place of ioutil.ReadFile. Then you can supply run with the file contents right here instead of making the reader look at multiple other files just to understand one test case.\n\nDo you think the tests would be too dense if each one had to supply the names and contents of their files to the run function (plus presumably a list of which names should be considered stdlib)?",
      "revId": "d5002387142b1a3aebf8aa7d3022804a157d6ba0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
